$ SQL Server: datatype varchar

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/versions/2019 has full support for storing → development/Unicode/UTF-8 characters in a `varchar`. The
→ development/Unicode/collation must be set to a value with an `utf8` suffix, for example `latin1_general_100_ci_as_sc_utf8`.

{ Concatenating strings

  Two varchars can be concatenated with the `+` operator:
  gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/data-types/varchar/plus.sql||

}

sa:

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/nvarchar[nvarchar]

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[data types]
